---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getStrings } from '../../i18n';
const t = getStrings(Astro.currentLocale);
const crumbs = [{ label: t.nav.about }];
---

<Base title={t.about.title} crumbs={crumbs}>
  <h1>{t.about.title}</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>{t.about.unofficialTitle}</h2>
    <p>
      This is an independent study aid, <strong>not affiliated with any official institution, monastic order, or
      sect</strong>. Content rests on authoritative sources; AI-assisted material is clearly marked.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>{t.about.sourcesTitle}</h2>
    <table class="src-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Data</th><th>Source</th><th>License</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Pāli text & segmentation</td>
          <td><a href="https://suttacentral.net" rel="noopener">SuttaCentral</a> bilara-data (Mahāsaṅgīti edition)</td>
          <td class="data">Public domain / CC0</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Pāli grammar · roots · glosses</td>
          <td><a href="https://digitalpalidictionary.github.io" rel="noopener">Digital Pāḷi Dictionary (DPD)</a></td>
          <td class="data">CC BY-NC-SA 4.0</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Chinese Āgama (Madhyama)</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.cbeta.org" rel="noopener">CBETA</a></td>
          <td class="data">CC BY-NC-SA 3.0 TW</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Proper names</td>
          <td>
            <a href="https://github.com/mbingenheimer/buddhist_studies_glossaries" rel="noopener"
              >G. P. Malalasekera, Dictionary of Pāli Proper Names (DPPN)</a
            >
          </td>
          <td class="data">Public domain</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Offline semantic model</td>
          <td>
            <a href="https://huggingface.co/intfloat/multilingual-e5-small" rel="noopener"
              >intfloat / multilingual-e5-small</a
            > (same model at build and in-browser)
          </td>
          <td class="data">MIT</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="calm-note">
      The Chinese gloss, summaries, study cards, usage notes, and curated reranking are AI-assisted, generated from the
      source texts above; <strong>no third-party human translation is used</strong>, so no third-party translation
      licenses are involved. Named scholarly citations appear in the references on the World page.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>{t.about.licenseTitle}</h2>
    <p>
      Sources include <span class="data">CC BY-NC-SA</span> material (DPD, CBETA), which require
      <strong>attribution · non-commercial · share-alike</strong>. Share-alike propagates to the whole derived database,
      so this site is <strong>non-commercial</strong> and its derived data is released under the same terms; DPPN and the
      Pāli edition are public domain, and the embedding model is MIT — all compatible.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>{t.about.aiTitle}</h2>
    <p class="calm-note">{t.common.aiContentNote}</p>
    <p>
      The line: <strong>facts come from the source texts and dictionary (the authoritative layer, never rewritten by
      AI)</strong>; <strong>interpretation goes through the AI-assisted layer (gloss / summary / study cards), each time
      grounded in the real grammar of the source and reviewed before publication</strong>. Background and history are
      cited by name, with points of no consensus marked as such.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="dedication" aria-label="dedication of merit">
    <h2>{t.about.dedicationTitle}</h2>
    <p class="calm-note dedication-note">{t.about.dedicationNote}</p>
    <blockquote class="dedication-verse">
      {t.about.dedicationVerse.map((line) => <span>{line}</span>)}
    </blockquote>
    <p class="dedication-source calm-note">{t.about.dedicationSource}</p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  section { margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
  h2 { font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .src-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .src-table th, .src-table td { text-align: start; padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); vertical-align: top; }
  .src-table th { font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .dedication { margin-top: var(--space-8); padding-top: var(--space-6); border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .dedication-note { margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .dedication-verse { margin: 0; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-1); font-family: var(--font-zh); font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--ink-soft); text-align: center; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .dedication-source { text-align: center; margin-top: var(--space-3); }
</style>
